            "function",
            "reuse",
            "abstraction"
          ]
        },
        {
          "trigger": "first_failure",
          "title": "The helper should do one clear job",
          "body": "If the function is hard to reuse, it may be doing too much. A good first function here is a small transfer action that can be called again when needed.",
          "concepts": [
            "single responsibility",
            "helper action"
          ]
        },
        {
          "trigger": "repeated_failure",
          "title": "Reuse beats copy-paste thinking",
          "body": "This level teaches a structural idea: once a sequence is valid, you should call it again instead of rebuilding the same logic each time in the main flow.",
